revision.text:
{{Infobox news event |title = 2013 Moscow Psychiatric Hospital Fire |image = Map of Russia - Moscow Oblast (2008-03).svg |image_size = 250px |caption = Location of Moscow Oblast in Russia |date = April 26, 2013 |time = 2:30 Moscow Time (22:30 UTC) |place = [[Moscow Oblast]], [[Russia]] |coordinates = 56_34_22_N_37_13_26_E_ |also known as = April 2013 Russian Hospital fire |cause = unknown, may have been caused by a patient |reported injuries = 3 |reported death(s) = 38 }}
The '''2013 Moscow psychiatric hospital fire''' occurred on 26 April 2013 at 2:30 am Moscow Time (22:30 UTC). At least 38 people were killed, included 36 patients and two doctors after fires tore through a [[psychiatric]] [[hospital]] outside [[Moscow]] in the village of Ramenskyon, 70 miles north of [[Moscow]] in [[Moscow Oblast]] on April 26, 2013. 29 people were burned alive, killing some patients in their beds and others who were trapped by barred windows. Only 3 people survived, including 2 patients and a nurse.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://rt.com/news/patients-killed-moscow-psychiatric-hospital-fire-421/ |title=Dozens dead in psych ward fire near Moscow, 3 survive |agency=[[RT (TV network)|RT News]] |date=April 26, 2013 |accessdate=April 28, 2013 |archivedate=April 29, 2013 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130429042649/http://rt.com/news/patients-killed-moscow-psychiatric-hospital-fire-421/ |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-22304728 |title=Blaze kills 38 at psychiatric hospital near Moscow |publisher=[[BBC News]] |date=April 26, 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130428143430/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-22304728 |deadurl=no |archivedate=April 28, 2013 |accessdate=April 28, 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2013/04/25/world/europe/russia-psychiatric-hospital-fire/index.html |title=38 people dead in fire at psychiatric hospital in Russia |author=Clare Sebastian |agency=[[CNN]] |date=April 25, 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130430080430/http://edition.cnn.com/2013/04/25/world/europe/russia-psychiatric-hospital-fire/index.html |archivedate=April 30, 2013 |deadurl=no |accessdate=April 26, 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://en.ria.ru/russia/20130426/180855099/38-People-Die-in-Clinic-Fire-Near-Moscow--Health-Ministry.html |title=Fire at Psychiatric Clinic Near Moscow Kills 38 |place=Russia |agency=[[RIA Novosti]] |date=April 26, 2013 |accessdate=April 28, 2013 |archivedate=April 30, 2013 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130430214805/http://en.ria.ru/russia/20130426/180855099/38-People-Die-in-Clinic-Fire-Near-Moscow--Health-Ministry.html |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Alexei Anishchuk |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2013/04/26/us-russia-fire-idUSBRE93P02P20130426 |title=Fire kills dozens in Russian psychiatric hospital |agency=[[Reuters]] |date=April 26, 2013 |accessdate=April 28, 2013 |archivedate=April 28, 2013 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130428202453/https://www.reuters.com/article/2013/04/26/us-russia-fire-idUSBRE93P02P20130426 |df= }}</ref>
==Fire== The fire broke out on the 26th April 2013 at 2:30 Moscow Time (22:30 UTC) in a psychiatric hospital near Moscow in a village called Ramenskyon. Ramenskyon is located approximately 70 miles north of Moscow in the Moscow Oblast in European Russia. The fire ignited on the 2nd floor of the 2 story building in a patient's bed. 3 doctors and 1 nurse ran to the bed but were burned alive immediately. The fire raged through the 2nd floor and killed everyone on that floor. 6 minutes later, the 2nd floor collapsed and crushed patients on the ground floor. 4 minutes later, the fire services reached the hospital and spent the next 3 hours extinguishing the blaze. When the fire finally settled in the morning, the fire brigade broke into the building and searched for survivors but only found 3 injured people alive: a nurse on the 1st floor and 2 patients on the ground floor.
