{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}} {{Use Indian English|date=September 2018}} {{Infobox organization | name = Accident Care and Transport Service | bgcolor = <!-- header background color --> | fgcolor = <!-- header text color --> | image = | image_border = | size = <!-- default 200px --> | alt = <!-- alt text; see [[WP:ALT]] --> | caption = | map = <!-- optional --> | msize = <!-- map size, optional, default 250px --> | malt = <!-- map alt text --> | mcaption = <!-- optional --> | map2 = | abbreviation = ACTS | motto = [[Nishkam Karma]] | predecessor = | successor = | formation = 2000 | extinction = <!-- date of extinction, optional --> | type = [[Nonprofit organization|NPO]] | status = <!-- ad hoc, treaty, foundation, etc --> | purpose = <!-- focus as e.g. humanitarian, peacekeeping, etc --> | headquarters = [[Thrissur]] city, [[Kerala]] | location = | coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> | region_served = [[Thrissur]] city and [[Thrissur District]] | membership = Free | language = <!-- official languages --> | general = <!-- Secretary General --> | leader_title = Chairman | leader_name = | leader_title2 = | leader_name2 = | leader_title3 = | leader_name3 = | leader_title4 = | leader_name4 = | key_people = Fr. [[Davis Chiramel]], Director | main_organ = <!-- gral. assembly, board of directors, etc --> | parent_organization = <!-- if one --> | affiliations = <!-- if any --> | budget = | num_staff = | num_volunteers = 17,000 | website = http://accidentcare.in/Default.aspx | remarks = | former name = }}
'''Accident Care and Transport Service''' or '''ACTS''' ([[Malayalam]]: ആക്ട്‌സ് )is a voluntary organisation providing free emergency assistance to accident victims in [[Thrissur]] city and [[Thrissur District]] of [[India]].<ref>{{cite news |date=13 August 2012 |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-kerala/extend-help-to-road-accident-victims-says-minister/article3761103.ece |title=Extend help to road accident victims, says Minister |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=2014-08-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-kerala/legal-tangles-should-not-come-in-way-of-helping-accident-victims/article943361.ece |title=‘Legal tangles should not come in way of helping accident victims' |work=The Hindu | date=10 December 2010 |accessdate=2014-08-29}}</ref><ref name=equip>{{cite web |url=http://www.hindu.com/2008/10/17/stories/2008101761520300.htm |title=Police ill-equipped to handle trauma cases |publisher=The Hindu |date=17 October 2008 |accessdate=2014-08-29}}</ref> ==History== ACTS was founded on 8 May 2000, under the leadership of Fr. [[Davis Chiramel]]<ref name=award>{{cite web|url=http://mattersindia.com/kidney-priest-gets-another-award/ |title=Kidney priest gets another award |publisher=Matters India |date=13 May 2013 |accessdate=2014-08-29 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140903113813/http://mattersindia.com/kidney-priest-gets-another-award/ |archivedate=3 September 2014 }}</ref><ref name=carvalho>{{cite news |url=http://www.asianews.it/index.php?l=en&art=16393 |title=Catholic priest donates kidney to save Hindu man |work=[[AsiaNews]] |date=22 September 2009 |accessdate=2014-08-29 |first=Nirmala |last=Carvalho}}</ref> with the support of Alkesh Kumar Sarma, then [[District Collector]] of [[Thrissur District]], and civic leaders. Till 2014, ACTS has 17,000 members in 15 branches, 130 units and has 15 ambulances.<ref name=T1>{{cite news |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Road-accident-cases-Centre-can-follow-path-outlined-by-Thrissur/articleshow/44904839.cms |title=Road accident cases: Centre can follow path outlined by Thrissur |date=22 October 2014 |first=Dipak K |last=Dash |newspaper=Times of India |accessdate=28 September 2018}}</ref>
==Thrissur Model== The [[Supreme court|Supreme Court]] appointed K Skandan Committee for making comprehensive guideline for ''Good Samaritans'' has appraised the role for Accident Care and Transport Service for their valuable contribution to the society. In its report submitted to [[Supreme court|Supreme Court]], the Committee has recommended the Thrissur model of ''Good Samaritans''. If the recommendations are accepted by the apex court, [[Thrissur]] Model of ''Good Samaritans'' will be followed all over [[India]].<ref name=T1 /><ref>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Road-accident-cases-Good-days-ahead-for-Good-Samaritans/articleshow/44904362.cms |title=Road accident cases: Good days ahead for Good Samaritans |publisher=Times of India |accessdate=2014-10-25}}</ref>
