{{orphan|date=May 2017}}
'''James E. Banta''' is an American health scientist and the first to cultivate dengue virus in tissue culture and to demonstrate cytopathogenic effect, was the Dean, School of Public Health and Tropical Medicine from [[Tulane University]] subsequently after being Elected as Fellow at the [[American Association for the Advancement of Science]] in 1959.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.aaas.org/fellow/banta-james-e |title=James E. Banta |publisher=aaas.org |accessdate=May 13, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://libguides.tulane.edu/famousalumni/jebanta |title=James E. Banta |publisher=tulane.edu |accessdate=May 13, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.acpm.org/person/11435229/George-Washington-University-James-Banta.htm |title=James Banta |publisher=acpm.org |accessdate=May 13, 2017}}</ref>

